SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 118
BY SENATOR BARROW
COMMENDATIONS. Commends and congratulates Etta Jane Harris on her retirement.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend and congratulate Etta Jane Harris for more than forty-four years of exceptional
3 public service upon the occasion of her retirement.
4 WHEREAS, Etta Jane Harris began her distinguished career in state government in
5 1979, at the age of nineteen, embarking upon more than forty-four years of dedicated public
6 service; and
7 WHEREAS, throughout her remarkable tenure, Ms. Harris has been a steadfast
8 advocate for single-family housing, access to public services, children in the child welfare
9 system, individuals with disabilities, and people who are hungry and in need; and
10 WHEREAS, she earned a Bachelor of Science in Business Management and a Master
11 of Public Administration, with a concentration in budget and finance, from Southern
12 University and A&M College; and
13 WHEREAS, she has served with distinction as a state budget manager for the
14 commissioner of administration under several administrations, providing expertise across
15 numerous policy areas, including education, juvenile justice, special schools, social services,
16 and coordinated system care; and
17 WHEREAS, Ms. Harris' exceptional leadership led to her appointment as deputy
18 undersecretary of the Louisiana Department of Children and Family Services, where she
