1 often presented information to, or testified before, legislators, members of the judiciary,
2 advocacy organizations, and professional audiences; and
3 WHEREAS, she was appointed to serve as a member on several significant bodies,
4 including the Education Estimating Conference Committee, the Children's Cabinet, and the
5 Juvenile Justice Committee, further demonstrating her trusted expertise and meaningful
6 influence in state governance; and
7 WHEREAS, widely respected by colleagues and peers, Ms. Harris is known not only
8 for her professional accomplishments but also for her mentorship, impeccable style,
9 commanding presence, and ability to uplift those around her; and
10 WHEREAS, her warmth, humor, kindness, energy, and gracious spirit have enriched
11 the lives of all who have had the privilege of working with her; and
12 WHEREAS, as she transitions into a well-earned retirement, she looks forward to
13 traveling, maintaining her passion for fitness, pursuing activities such as running, biking, and
14 swimming, and spending time with friends and family, including her two beloved sons.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
16 does hereby commend and congratulate Etta Jane Harris for her more than forty-four years
17 of exemplary public service and does hereby extend best wishes for a fulfilling and joyful
18 retirement.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Etta
20 Jane Harris.
